The paper deals with the complexity of a reconfiguration problem for list edge-colorings of graphs, which involves changing the color assignment of a single edge at a time. This problem is closely related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, and involves analyzing the computational complexity of finding a sequence of valid colorings between two given colorings. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the problem involves analyzing the structure of planar graphs and their colorings, which suggests the sub-category cs.GT (Graph Theory) as another likely option. Finally, the paper also involves analyzing the hardness of the problem for different parameter values, which suggests the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible option.
